author: igv4321
body:
It has now become apparent that TDC codes 50-57 are not supposed to happen during normal QIE10/QIE11 operation. This PR introduces a special invalid code for them. Minor changes might happen for data. No changes are expected for MC.

The plot below is courtesy Jim Hirschauer. Quoting him, "it looks like 51 and 55 might be most common, 50, 52, 53, 56 are less common, and 54, 57 dont happen".

![hfm_qie10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5552377/33523994-b9fa5f74-d7d9-11e7-8f0b-2fb4a1ada12a.png)
title: Adding special treatment for QIE10/QIE11 TDC values 50 to 57
